uhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn the medieval period, the monarch was seen as the embodiment of the community of his kingdom, the body politic. And while we've long since shed that view, it nonetheless continues to influence our understanding of contemporary politics. This book offers thirteen case studies from premodern and contemporary Europe that demonstrate the process through which political corporations-bodies politic-were and continue to be constructed and challenged. Drawing on  history, archaeology, literary criticism, and art history, the contributors survey a wide geographical and chronological spectrum to offer a panoramic view of these dynamic political entities.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aMroziewicz, Karolina, eeditor.1 aSroczynski, Aleksander, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2017z978311066284908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press  eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060644740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048533282zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048533282.jpg  a978-3-11-060644-7  Amsterdam University Press  eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  AUP eBook Package 2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG